15 JuneGovernment will hold a series of ministerial cluster media briefings to report and update the nation on the progress made around implementation of the Programme of Action since the State of the Nation Address. The briefings will highlight the clusters contribution to Government s strategic priorities. The briefings will take place at the Imbizo Media Centre, 120 Plein Street in Cape Town or GCIS Auditorium, 1st Floor, Midtown Building, cnr. Sisulu and Madiba Streets, Pretoria from 18 June to 22 June 2012. There will be a simultaneous video link up to both venues. Briefings schedule: Monday, 18 June 2012 (Pretoria) 10h00-11h30: Social Protection and Community Development Cluster (Chairperson: Minister of Social Development) Tuesday, 19 June 2012 (Pretoria) (Postponed until further notice) 10h00-11h30: Economic Sectors and Employment cluster briefing (Chairperson: Minister of Rural Development and Land Reform) Wednesday, 20 June 2012 (Cape Town) (Postponed until further notice) 10h00-11h30: International Cooperation, Trade and Security cluster briefing (Chairperson: Minister of Defence and Military Veterans) Thursday, 21 June 2012 (Cape Town) (Postponed until further notice) 10h00-11h30: Human Development cluster briefing (Chairperson: Minister of Basic Education) Friday, 22 June 2012 (Pretoria) (Postponed until further notice) 10h00 -11h30: Governance and Administration (Chairperson: Minister of Home Affairs Deputy Chairperson) RSVP: Shadi Baloyi on shadib@gcis.gov.za or 0769467136 (Pretoria) /Sbongile Dalasile on sbongile@gcis.gov.za or 071 292 1006 (Cape Town)Enquiries: Mzobanzi Jikazana (Pretoria) Cell: 083 641 2355 Liezil Cerf (Cape Town) Cell: 076 778 2380 Issued by: Government Communications (GCIS)